<br>
So, what's a Friar?<br>
A Friar is a guy in leather armor that can buff, heal, and thump things with a stick.  But there's more than one way to make a Friar.<br>
<br>
Friars get 1.0 spec points per level and have four skills to put them in:  Enhancement, Rejuvenation, Staff, Parry.  No matter how you look at it, something is gonna come up hurtin' but not necessarily hurting all that bad.<br>
<br>
The first question to answer is:  How am I gonna play DAoC?<br>
 A) Are you going to group 90% of the time?<br>
 B) Are you going to solo 90% of the time?<br>
 C) Do you want to be fairly effective at both?<br>
<br>
In RvR, a Friar A is going to be in the healing/rezing role, only fighting as a last resort.  Friar B is going to be thumping casters in RvR.  Friar C is likely going to heal a bit to keep the tanks rolling early on then hit stamina-regen and join the fray.  <br>
<br>
There are of course, variations on each theme.  Friar C will most likely lean one way or the other a little bit and Friars A and B will most likely not be *fully* speced.  The key is, of course, to fit your skills to how you want to play.<br>
<br>
There are two phases to specing your course.  Phase 1 is level 39.  Phase 2 is level 50.  Since levels 40-50 give half-again the spec points for that level as you pass half-way, you have greater flexibility to &quot;flesh out&quot; skills you neglected earlier.  Key, of course, is Phase 1.<br>
<br>
Conventional wisdom is 2/3 spec (which at 50 is 33 or 34) is sufficient to not weaken the character while giving sufficient points to allocate other places to balance the character.<br>
<br>
Let's look at Friar C based on 2/3 spec.<br>
Staff to 34 (to get Holy Staff)<br>
Rejuv to 33 (to get Major Refection)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> then either:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enhance to 24 (to get Shield of Zeal)<br>
Parry to 8 (leftover)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> or </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enhance to 12 (to get Saint's Energy **)<br>
Parry to 22<br>
or some combination of.<br>
<br>
Now that's a pretty respectable Friar.  Very good healing with the Rejuv (Major heals are not subject to variation like the lesser and normal heal line), good damage, reasonable buffing and parry ***<br>
<br>
Friar A, le grouping Friar, will sacrifice Staff to gain better healing and enhance, or perhaps just better healing. (Rejuv to 42, Enhance to 12, Staff to 30 or Rejuv to 43, Staff to 32).  The logic here is, simply, in a group with a Cleric, a friar will be doing some buffing and definitely backup healing when the spam hits the fan or the cleric gets agroed.  Due to the low staff skill, soloing won't be a high priority for this guy.<br>
<br>
Friar B, le solo friar, will sacrifice healing for staff and enhance for better damage and self-protection and use the normal heal line for after-combat healing.  He'll look something like Enhance 30**, Staff 44 (sweet long-term stun style), Parry 8.  Basic logic hers is: kill it before it kills you.  Simple, no frills, and deadly.  <br>
<br>
About that &quot;deadly&quot; bit.  Solo, he is.  In a group, he is...to himself, unless he's very skilled (think Ranger in EQ).  If you're grouped with tanks who are 3+ levels above you, you're golden.  Less, and you had <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> better</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> watch your self because you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> get the shiznitz agroed out of you.  If you Friar's Friend, get agroed, and then chain to Banish instead of switching to Friar's Redress...tell the cleric to save mana, you ARE gonna go down and no one's gonna get that thing off ya <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (I screwed this up once myself and even pally heal-chant couldn't get it off me)  If you're highly speced in staff, your damage will be on-par or better than armsman's -- if nothing else, your agro will be unless you are careful.  Always, always keep Friar's Redress handy; it's worth the detaunt and defense boost.<br>
<br>
- - -<br>
<br>
Me? I'm the thump-'em-till-they-squeal type who would like to survive in a group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I went heavy staff (lots of soloing at low levels) with 7 both in Rejuv (CURE!!) and Enhance -- in retrospect I should have gone to 8 Rejuv for the major heal but hindsight is called that for a reason.<br>
<br>
Currently at lvl 32 I'm:<br>
 - Enhance 7<br>
 - Rejuv 15<br>
 - Staff 27<br>
 - Parry 1<br>
 <br>
 I'll keep staff 5 levels behind till I reach 29 staff (Friar's Boon) then bring Rejuv to 18 (again, Major heal line spell at 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  I can <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> stress enough the difference from 7 rejuv to 11 rejuv with the heal...a constant 136 points beats 158, 149, 26, 27, 40 ANY day.<br>
<br>
Plan for Level 39<br>
 - Enhance 7<br>
 - Rejuv 19<br>
 - Staff 33<br>
 - Parry 1<br>
 <br>
 Obviously I'm planning more for the &quot;smash them quick&quot; approach, though the heal at 18 rejuv should keep me doing well in my role as backup healer.<br>
 <br>
Plan(s) for 50<br>
 - Enhance 12 **<br>
 - Rejuv 25<br>
 - Staff 44<br>
 - Parry 14<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
 - Enhance 12<br>
 - Rejuv 33<br>
 - Staff 39<br>
 - Parry 12<br>
 <br>
Haven't decided yet.<br>
<br>
Obviously I don't see much use for the enhance line.  If I had more points I'd definitely put them in there and dump the rest to parry -- I don't think enhance sucks as some have said, I just think staff and rejuv are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> more</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> important, at least to the way I play.  I rarely solo for leveling-quality exp, just for cash to throw away at the Tailor merchant. :P  I also find myself being the sole healer in groups frequently.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Friar &quot;Must Haves&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Enhance 2: Endurance regen is the BOMB! Speed is nice but endurance is b-e-t-t-e-r.  In RvR, if you have no healing duties, toss this bugger on and rush into battle.  You'll be thumping the daylights out of them long after they're OOE.  In a good group with lots of mobs, it's a tossup but if you've got a healer (or two) you trust at the helm, flip this on and you'll be styling during the entire train.<br>
<br>
Rejuv 7:  You can't live without cure poison and disease.  This should be obvious. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Rejuv 15: While not an <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> absolute</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;must have&quot; it is definitely part of the arsenal you should have.  There is nothing worse than rezzing someone only to have them die 3 seconds later b/c of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> one</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> swipe from a walk-on mob.  With the low-hp version, they can run to the other side of the party and let someone else gain agro while they're lunch meat with the nearly-no-hp version.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, that's MY take on the Friar.  <br>
<br>
<br>
